sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    participant Operator as Training Operator<br/>(controller-runtime)
    participant Master as Master Pod<br/>(via headless Service)
    participant Worker as Worker Pod(s)<br/>(via headless Service)

    Note over User,Worker: Flow 1: Training Job Lifecycle (PyTorch/TF/XGBoost/JAX/Paddle)

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl create pytorchjob<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kubeconfig
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-pytorchjob<br/>HTTPS/9443 TLS (self-signed)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admit / Reject
    K8sAPI-->>User: Job created

    Note over Operator: Informer watch detects new CR

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create headless Services<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create PodGroup (optional gang scheduling)<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Master Pod<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pod(s)<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA Token

    Worker->>Master: Distributed training communication<br/>TCP/framework port (no encryption)
    Master-->>Worker: Gradient sync / parameter updates

    Note over Operator: Monitors pod status via informer

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update job status<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA Token

    Note over User,Worker: Flow 2: PyTorch Elastic Training

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Master Pod<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods with init container<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update HPA<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA Token

    Note over Worker: Init container waits for master DNS

    Worker->>Master: DNS probe (init container)<br/>TCP/23456
    Master-->>Worker: Master available

    Worker->>Master: c10d rendezvous<br/>TCP/23456 (no encryption)
    Master-->>Worker: Rendezvous complete

    Note over User,Worker: Flow 3: MPI Job Execution

    participant Launcher as Launcher Pod

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create ConfigMap (hostfile + kubexec)<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create SA + Role + RoleBinding<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Launcher + Worker Pods<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA Token

    Launcher->>K8sAPI: pods/exec on workers (via kubexec)<br/>HTTPS/6443 per-job SA Token
    Launcher->>Worker: MPI communication<br/>TCP/9999 (no encryption)
    Worker-->>Launcher: MPI results
